SUPPORT COMMUNICATION - SECURITY BULLETIN

Document ID: c00553092
Version: 3

HPSBUX01231 SSRT051041 Revised - HP-UX Mozilla Remote Unauthorized
           Execution of Privileged Code or Denial of Service (DoS)

NOTICE: The information in this Security Bulletin should be acted
        upon as soon as possible.

Release Date: 2005-10-03
Last Updated: 2005-11-08

Potential Security Impact: Remote execution of privileged code or
Denial of Service (DoS)

Source: Hewlett-Packard Company,
        HP Software Security Response Team

VULNERABILITY SUMMARY
A potential security vulnerability has been identified with HP-UX
running Mozilla, where the vulnerability could be exploited to
allow a remote, unauthorized user to execute privileged code or to
create a Denial of Service (DoS).

References: CAN-2005-2871, MFSA 2005-57

SUPPORTED SOFTWARE VERSIONS*: ONLY impacted versions are listed.
HP-UX B.11.00, B.11.11, B.11.22, B.11.23 running Mozilla 1.7.11
and previous.

BACKGROUND

 ->Mozilla for HP-UX version 1.7.12.01 is now available,
addressing the following:
MFSA 2005-57 IDN heap overrun using soft-hyphens

 ->HP-UX Mozilla 1.7.12.01 also addresses all the potential
vulnerabilities resolved by Mozilla 1.7.12 and previous.

 ->More information about those potential vulnerabilities is
available here:
http://www.mozilla.org/projects/security/
known-vulnerabilities.html#Mozilla

To determine if an HP-UX system has an affected version,
search the output of "swlist -a revision -l fileset"
for one of the filesets listed below. For affected systems
verify that the recommended action has been taken.

AFFECTED VERSIONS

HP-UX B.11.00
HP-UX B.11.11
HP-UX B.11.22
HP-UX B.11.23
=============
Mozilla.MOZ-COM
action: install 1.7.12.01 or subsequent

END AFFECTED VERSIONS

RESOLUTION

- ->HP has made Mozilla version 1.7.12.01 available to resolve the
 potential vulnerabilities. It can be downloaded from
http://www.hp.com/go/mozilla.

 ->NOTE: Customers who installed the preliminary version of 1.7.12
         from Mozilla.org should install Mozilla 1.7.12.01 as
         described above. The preliminary version was discussed in
         Update 1 of this Security Bulletin.

MANUAL ACTIONS:Yes - Update
 ->Update to HP Mozilla 1.7.12.01 or subsequent.

PRODUCT SPECIFIC INFORMATION

HP-UX Security Patch Check: Security Patch Check revision B.02.00
analyzes all HP-issued Security Bulletins to provide a subset of
recommended actions that potentially affect a specific HP-UX
system. For more information:
http://www.software.hp.com/cgi-bin/swdepot_parser.cgi/cgi
displayProductInfo.pl?productnumber=B6834AAtN

UPDATE HISTORY
Initial release: 03 October 2005
Update 1: 12 October 2005 Preliminary Mozilla 1.7.12 available.
Update 2: 08 November 2005 Mozilla 1.7.12.01 available.


